02/09/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The generator of Unit 5 at Bulgaria's Kozloduy nuclear power plant was disconnected from the country's power distribution system on Saturday (September 1st), after the automated safety system of the 1,000-megawatt facility was activated. The incident did not result in any leaks, the plant's management said. Experts are currently investigating the reasons for the shutdown. (BNR, Darik, BGNES, AP, Sofia news agency, Focus - 01/09/07)
